CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 3, 1943, pg. 12, reads: "They'll Be Here When Daddy Comes Marching Home - Shown above are children of men overseas on missions for Uncle Sam. These men are from Pittsburgh and they have never seen their heirs.  Mrs. Laura Dawkins and Lucius, Jr., of 6933 Fifth avenue, gave their breadwinner to the Navy.  Center: Baby Ellen, four weeks old, is the daughter of Pfc. and Mrs. Lloyd Barnett, who lives on Somers street.  Right: Mrs. Rose Lee Cathie of 1521 Brushton avenue, proudly holds George W. Cathie, Jr.  His father, Corporal Cathie, is stationed in Iran. They gave - what are you doing? - Harris Photos" [Cutline order incorrect]
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Laura Dawkins posed holding Lucius Dawkins Jr., or Rose Lee Cathie posed holding George W. Cathie Jr., on arm of chair, in domestic interior with floral wallpaper
